snippet.textDisplay:
Thanks Coke Studio for this. "Shundori komola" can be such a beautiful song if done right.....even as a fusion.
I'm sorry but this one is an epic fail in my opinion. For people who understand bengali, this is not just a "Fusion". Its more of a "Con-fusion". The english part.....first of all...does it add anything to the melody? Also the lyrics have absolutely no similarity (meaning) with the main part "Shundori Komola" and goes on an unreachable tangent. To me its like...."Tears in Heaven" mixed with "Lungi dance"! The parts were very well performed on their own. But that's hardly the point of a "Fusion". May be a more cohesive version can be performed in the near future? Thanks
